value.value: Mitogen-activated protein kinase-binding protein 1 (1514 aa, ~164 kDa) is encoded by the human MAPKBP1 gene. This protein plays a role in protein-protein binding in Jun kinase signaling.
This gene is involved in cadherin binding and development of embryonic axial midline structures in vertebrates.

Human COBLL1 wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 2q24.3 and is approximately 190 kb in length. This allele, which encodes cordon-bleu protein-like 1 protein, plays a role in the development of the neural tube and notochord and cadherin binding.
